Ext.data.JsonP['Platform_Marketplace']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Platform Marketplace</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p></div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-49157965\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Platform Marketplace</h1>\n    <p>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Overview\">Overview</a>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Marketplaceaccessandpublishing\">Marketplace access and publishing</a>    </p>\n</li></ul></li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-CLIoptions\">CLI options</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Installamodel\">Install a model</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Installaconnector\">Install a connector</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Installablock\">Install a block</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_safe-id-UGxhdGZvcm1NYXJrZXRwbGFjZS1TZWFyY2hpbmdmb3Jtb2RlbHMsY29ubmVjdG9ycyxhbmRibG9ja3M\">Searching for models, connectors, and blocks</a>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-CLIsearchsuggestions\">CLI search suggestions</a>    </p>\n</li></ul></li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Platform_Marketplace-section-src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Pre-builtconnectors\">Pre-built connectors</a>    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>This document provides an overview of the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a>    <span style=\"color: #333333;\">\n.    </span>\n    </p>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Overview\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Overview</span></h2>\n    <p>The <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a> is a repository of building blocks for both Apps and APIs. Developers can discover and install components from the Marketplace, and they can also publish new components. The <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a> supports setting the access policy of a component. The following access policies are supported:    </p>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p><tt class=\" \">public</tt>: Everyone can see it (even those outside of your organization).    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><tt class=\" \">private</tt>: Only the publisher see it. This is the default policy when a component is first published.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><tt class=\" \">org</tt>: Only certain organizations can see it. Organizations can be added or removed to/from a component via the <tt class=\" \">appc org </tt>command.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><tt class=\" \">user_or_org</tt>: Only certain organizations or users can see it. Users can be added or removed to/from a component via the <tt class=\" \">appc user</tt> command, and Organizations can be added or removed to/from a component via the <tt class=\" \">appc org</tt> command.    </p>\n</li></ul>    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Marketplaceaccessandpublishing\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Marketplace access and publishing</span></h3>\n    <p>You can access the Platform Marketplace in the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a> or via the Appcelerator CLI.    </p>\n    <p>To publish something to the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a>, you must use the Appcelerator CLI.    </p>\n    <p>Currently, the Platform Marketplace supports the following component types:    </p>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p><tt class=\" \">Blocks</tt>: Used for building APIs    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><tt class=\" \">Connectors</tt>: Used for building APIs    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><tt class=\" \">Models</tt>: Used for building APIs    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>At the time of publishing this document, we do not support mobile app modules and Allow widgets.    </p>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-CLIoptions\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>CLI options</span></h2>\n    <p>The Appcelerator CLI provides a number of options for interacting with the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a> from the command line. The table below outlines the commands that can be used:    </p>\n    <div class=\"tablewrap\">\n        <table class=\"confluenceTable\">\n        <thead class=\" \">    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTh\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Name    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTh\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Arguments    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTh\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Description    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n</thead><tfoot class=\" \"/><tbody class=\" \">    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>search    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>[search_term]    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Search the Marketplace for a particular component or set of components.    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>install    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>[component_name]    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Install a specific component. Execute this command from within an API project. The CLI will ensure the component is installed in the proper location (i.e., models will be installed in the <tt class=\" \">models</tt> directory and connectors in the <tt class=\" \">connectors</tt> directory).    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>publish    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>None    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Publish a component to the Marketplace. Execute this command from the root directory of your component project.    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>unpublish    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>[component_name]    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Unpublish a component from the Marketplace. The [compononent_name] is only needed when the command is executed outside the component&#x2019;s project directory.    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>access    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>get or set    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Get the current access policy or set it. The valid values are: <tt class=\" \">public</tt>, <tt class=\" \">private</tt>, <tt class=\" \">org</tt>, and <tt class=\" \">user_or_org</tt>. Defaults to <tt class=\" \">private</tt>.    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>org    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>add, rm, or ls    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Add, remove or list the current organizations tied to your component. Note: the <tt class=\" \">org</tt> values are only relevant if your access policy is set to <tt class=\" \">org</tt> or <tt class=\" \">org_or_user</tt>.    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>user    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>add, rm, or ls    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Add, remove or list the current users tied to your component. Note: the <tt class=\" \">user</tt> values are only relevant if your access policy is set to <tt class=\" \">user_or_org.</tt>    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>owner    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>add, rm, or ls    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Add, remove or list the current owners tied to your component. Owners can set/change values for the <tt class=\" \">access</tt>, <tt class=\" \">org</tt> and <tt class=\" \">user</tt> commands.    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n</tbody>        </table>\n            </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Installamodel\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Install a model</span></h2>\n    <p>To install an existing Model from the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a>, execute the following command from within your API project: <tt class=\" \">appc install model/model_name</tt>    </p>\n    <p>The <tt class=\" \">install</tt> command will place the model in the <tt class=\" \">models</tt> directory of your project.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Installaconnector\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Install a connector</span></h2>\n    <p>To install an existing Connector from the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a>, execute the following command from within your API project: <tt class=\" \">appc install &lt;connector/connector_name&gt;</tt>    </p>\n    <p>The <tt class=\" \">install</tt> command will place the connector in the <tt class=\" \">connectors</tt> directory of your project.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Installablock\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Install a block</span></h2>\n    <p>To install an existing Block from the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a>, run the following command from within your API project: <tt class=\" \">appc install &lt;block/block_name&gt;</tt>    </p>\n    <p>The <tt class=\" \">install</tt> command will place the block in the <tt class=\" \">blocks</tt> directory of your project.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-49157965_safe-id-UGxhdGZvcm1NYXJrZXRwbGFjZS1TZWFyY2hpbmdmb3Jtb2RlbHMsY29ubmVjdG9ycyxhbmRibG9ja3M\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Searching for models, connectors, and blocks</span></h2>\n    <p>Searching for models, connectors, and blocks can be accomplished by two different methods: using the CLI search command or searching directly in the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Marketplace</a>.    </p>\n    <p>If you are unsure of the exact name, you can search the Marketplace using the CLI: <tt class=\" \">appc search &lt;search_string&gt;</tt>    </p>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-CLIsearchsuggestions\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>CLI search suggestions</span></h3>\n    <p>When using <tt class=\" \">appc search</tt>, don&apos;t use wildcards. The search command uses a fuzzy search algorithm to return a list of components.    </p>\n    <p>If you know the component name starts with a certain string or character, try the <tt class=\" \">appc search sale</tt> command. This example will return the <tt class=\" \">connector/appc.salesforce</tt> connector.    </p>\n    <p>If you want to get a list of all the connectors, try the <tt class=\" \">appc search connector</tt> command. This example will return a list of all the available connectors.    </p>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-49157965_PlatformMarketplace-Pre-builtconnectors\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Pre-built connectors</span></h2>\n    <p>To see a list of the pre-built Connectors, please visit <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://software.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://software.appcelerator.com/</a>.    </p>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=49157965\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Platform Marketplace"});